:R-HSA-916853  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0009450 ;
        rdfs:comment        "GABA is metabolized in the mitochondrial matrix to succinate by the serial action of two enzymes, 4-aminobutyrate aminotransferase and suucinate semialdehyde dehydrogenase. Failure of the second reaction is associated with a rare human genetic disorder (Malaspina et al. 2016; Pearl et al. 2009)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Degradation of GABA" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Jassal, Bijay, 2019-07-15" , "Reviewed: Restituito, S, 2008-11-27 12:38:49" , "Edited: Mahajan, SS, 2010-06-29" , "Authored: Mahajan, SS, 2010-07-31" ;
